            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46267",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your fix makes the assumption that the configuration file is subdivided internally by the possible values of APPLICATION_ENV, which is not always the case.  If you are using the php\/inc suffix on your configuration files then Zend_Application assumes you will create a separate file for each value of APPLICATION_ENV and pass in the proper filename at runtime.  \r\n\r\nThat said, making this change would likely break backwards-compatibility for existing applications, so I would suggest bringing this issue up with the maintainer of Zend_Application (or it's successor) in ZF 2.0 to see if it can be addressed there. ",
